14 May 2002All media are invited to the opening of the George Multi-Purpose Community Centre (MPCC) in the Western Cape Province. The Western Cape Department of Social Services has invested R 5 million via the George Municipality for the construction of the MPCC. The centre has been in operation since August last year.An MPCC is a one-stop centre where local, provincial and national government, as well as other services are provided and relevant information to local communities.Journalists wishing to attend the launch are requested to reply no later than Thursday morning for transport arrangements.Venue: George MPCC Date: 18 May 2002 Time: 10:00Enquiries Lolo Maphophe Cell: 082 453 2857Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)